1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:36,995
{\an8}<i>Hello, Alex? We have a problem.</i>

2
00:00:45,587 --> 00:00:47,088
{\an8}<i>Let's go out after your class.</i>

3
00:00:49,382 --> 00:00:51,134
{\an8}Yes, if that's okay with you.

4
00:00:52,177 --> 00:00:54,846
{\an8}Why did you suddenly invite me?

5
00:00:54,929 --> 00:00:56,097
{\an8}What is that?

6
00:00:56,181 --> 00:00:57,974
{\an8}Do you have a problem with your mouth?
Like a mouth sore?

7
00:01:00,935 --> 00:01:02,103
{\an8}<i>Okay.</i>

8
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:16,242
{\an8}- You?!
- What?!

9
00:01:18,244 --> 00:01:21,873
{\an8}<i>Why did you assign Carlota</i>
<i>as Mikoy's secretary?</i>

10
00:01:23,208 --> 00:01:26,711
{\an8}<i>You're just doing this</i>
<i>to investigate him. Right?</i>

11
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:01,996
{\an8}Am I your boss?

12
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:25,854
{\an8}Oh?

13
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:28,231
{\an8}Why are you suddenly
so interested in Chiara?

14
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:30,692
{\an8}Because I have a strong feeling that--

15
00:02:36,447 --> 00:02:38,366
{\an8}I have a strong feeling that…

16
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:45,999
{\an8}she really likes cats.

17
00:02:49,919 --> 00:02:51,212
{\an8}Huh?

18
00:02:51,296 --> 00:02:52,881
{\an8}<i>Is that really what you wanted to say?</i>

19
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:59,137
{\an8}Alex, is there something I should know?

20
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:00,388
{\an8}Nothing!

21
00:03:00,471 --> 00:03:02,098
{\an8}I just wanted to say that

22
00:03:02,807 --> 00:03:04,267
{\an8}<i>you should get her a cat.</i>

23
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:06,978
{\an8}I think she's ready
to become a "meowi" again.

24
00:03:07,061 --> 00:03:10,899
{\an8}Look, things are pretty busy
at the office right now.

25
00:03:10,982 --> 00:03:13,109
{\an8}<i>I'll update you if anything new comes up.</i>

26
00:03:13,192 --> 00:03:14,986
{\an8}Just keep your phone with you.

27
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:19,782
{\an8}Wait, Alex!

28
00:03:23,578 --> 00:03:24,537
What is it?

29
00:03:44,015 --> 00:03:45,141
What?

30
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:47,185
Chiara!

31
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:23,388
There!

32
00:04:23,471 --> 00:04:24,806
The tension's finally released.

33
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:27,600
What happened?

34
00:04:27,684 --> 00:04:29,519
I was attacked, sir.

35
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:35,775
I got attacked
by mild-trentahin back pain.

36
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:39,529
But I'm okay now. Ma'am Chiara
is really good at massaging.

37
00:04:39,612 --> 00:04:40,905
Oh, wow!

38
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:44,659
So, what now? Are you okay now?

39
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:46,828
Yes, I'm okay!

40
00:04:46,911 --> 00:04:49,455
Thank you, Ma'am Chiara!

41
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,126
Feel better, okay?

42
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:57,297
I'll just get my bag.

43
00:05:00,258 --> 00:05:01,676
Thank you, Ma'am Chiara.

44
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:05,972
I'll study what misua is.

45
00:05:14,814 --> 00:05:16,232
Do you know each other?

46
00:05:24,991 --> 00:05:27,243
So I know her very well.

47
00:05:34,584 --> 00:05:36,335
What's misua?

48
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:39,172
Nothing!

49
00:05:40,548 --> 00:05:41,799
What is it really?

50
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:43,134
Don't you know?

51
00:05:43,217 --> 00:05:44,218
No.

52
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:45,845
It's noodles, like…

53
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,389
The thin ones.

54
00:05:48,473 --> 00:05:50,099
Is your friend really like that?

55
00:05:50,183 --> 00:05:51,309
Is he Indian or something!

56
00:05:51,392 --> 00:05:52,435
Hey, that's foul!

57
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:54,145
You might get bashed online.

58
00:05:55,354 --> 00:05:56,856
He really did something awful to me!

59
00:05:56,939 --> 00:05:59,484
I even prepared for this movie date.

60
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:01,069
And then what?!

61
00:06:01,152 --> 00:06:03,446
I bought a cute dress, did my makeup…

62
00:06:03,529 --> 00:06:06,449
I did everything to look presentable,

63
00:06:06,532 --> 00:06:07,825
and then he didn't show up?

64
00:06:07,909 --> 00:06:08,993
He acts like he's

65
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:10,661
- some kind of gift to women?
- Sofie.

66
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:13,331
If he did that,

67
00:06:13,414 --> 00:06:15,416
it's his loss, not yours.

68
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:20,338
No! No one's relaxing on this campus!

69
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:23,257
He'd better watch out for me.

70
00:06:23,341 --> 00:06:26,135
Only his eyes will come out unscathed!

71
00:06:26,219 --> 00:06:27,470
PHILIPPINE UNIVERSITY

72
00:06:27,553 --> 00:06:28,596
Sofie!

73
00:06:38,648 --> 00:06:40,858
You started this, so own it.

74
00:06:45,113 --> 00:06:46,280
This.

75
00:06:51,577 --> 00:06:53,996
General Ruiz passed through here.

76
00:07:23,025 --> 00:07:24,485
Bok, there are many like that.

77
00:07:43,045 --> 00:07:44,297
At the bar.

78
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:45,882
<i>When we were together.</i>

79
00:07:46,382 --> 00:07:47,884
<i>A glass fell.</i>

80
00:08:02,940 --> 00:08:04,692
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT

81
00:08:04,775 --> 00:08:07,737
And if she really is La Fornarina…

82
00:08:08,696 --> 00:08:11,782
and her family were to do something dirty…

83
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:17,538
I'd get close to someone clean,

84
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:19,624
someone innocent,

85
00:08:21,125 --> 00:08:22,793
someone like Mikoy,

86
00:08:22,877 --> 00:08:25,213
because that's the perfect cover.

87
00:08:43,814 --> 00:08:45,525
Everything you told me,

88
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:49,779
like timing,
the falling glass, the build-up,

89
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:50,988
gut feel…

90
00:08:51,072 --> 00:08:54,450
We still don't have any solid proof.

91
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:57,286
It's all just a gut feeling!

92
00:08:57,370 --> 00:08:58,204
Yes.

93
00:08:58,829 --> 00:09:01,582
Just feelings,
but I'm pretty sure about mine.

94
00:09:18,140 --> 00:09:20,309
You know what? I can't take this anymore.

95
00:09:25,273 --> 00:09:26,649
What were you thinking?

96
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:30,152
Sending your chihuahua after Mikoy.

97
00:09:30,236 --> 00:09:32,113
Mikoy, who doesn't even know.

98
00:09:32,196 --> 00:09:34,532
Mikoy, who can't even fix his eyebrows.

99
00:09:34,615 --> 00:09:38,661
Mikoy, whose only mistake
is loving our daughter!

100
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:45,126
And you think he won't find out?

101
00:09:45,209 --> 00:09:47,461
You're ruining your relationship
with your daughter.

102
00:10:01,851 --> 00:10:04,604
So you turned
her boyfriend into an operation.

103
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:06,856
Maybe you're forgetting, darling.

104
00:10:06,939 --> 00:10:09,358
You know how intense
our daughter can get when she's angry.

105
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:12,445
You also know she's
in love like this only now!

106
00:10:12,528 --> 00:10:16,490
And you know very well
what she is capable of--

107
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:24,206
What did you say?

108
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:38,638
You really call her a chihuahua?

109
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:53,611
But it's just that
I don't really like that girl.

110
00:11:08,334 --> 00:11:10,252
Chiara, tell me the truth.

111
00:11:12,129 --> 00:11:13,464
Mikoy?

112
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:18,761
Were you a masseuse before?

113
00:11:21,764 --> 00:11:23,224
Wow!

114
00:11:24,683 --> 00:11:26,060
How did you learn this?

115
00:11:27,728 --> 00:11:30,398
Seriously, sweetheart, you're really good.

116
00:11:30,481 --> 00:11:32,066
Nothing, I just…

117
00:11:32,858 --> 00:11:34,819
I just get lost

118
00:11:35,403 --> 00:11:39,824
in the reflexology rabbit hole online.

119
00:11:45,162 --> 00:11:47,373
Be careful with that Carlota.

120
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:50,418
Why though?

121
00:11:51,085 --> 00:11:52,044
What is she?

122
00:11:52,128 --> 00:11:53,337
A killer?

123
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:58,008
No, I just really don't like her,

124
00:11:58,092 --> 00:12:01,512
and I don't trust her,
so you shouldn't either.

125
00:12:11,647 --> 00:12:12,481
Right.

126
00:12:12,565 --> 00:12:15,734
You guys can start
bringing the things inside.

127
00:12:15,818 --> 00:12:16,777
Go ahead.

128
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:19,738
There's more of that.

129
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:25,494
Careful, okay? Be careful.

130
00:12:25,578 --> 00:12:27,288
Take care, mister.

131
00:12:27,371 --> 00:12:28,414
There.

132
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:30,916
Chiara?

133
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,049
That makes sense.

134
00:12:47,224 --> 00:12:49,393
Sir, there's more.

135
00:12:49,477 --> 00:12:50,811
Hurry.

136
00:12:51,770 --> 00:12:53,397
I'm so excited!

137
00:12:53,481 --> 00:12:55,441
There's more downstairs.

138
00:12:56,358 --> 00:12:57,818
That's two trucks.

139
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:06,952
Are you talking about me?

140
00:13:20,591 --> 00:13:23,093
I'm okay now, Alex.

141
00:13:31,435 --> 00:13:35,189
I'm good without the romantic traumas
and attachment issues,

142
00:13:35,272 --> 00:13:37,650
especially with you, Alex.

143
00:13:42,571 --> 00:13:45,824
But I can also say I want to try again.

144
00:13:45,908 --> 00:13:47,243
Ben!

145
00:14:00,381 --> 00:14:03,717
It's not you, okay?

146
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:06,428
La Fornarina.

147
00:14:06,512 --> 00:14:09,557
That's the topic
we're discussing, not you.

148
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,565
La Fornarina.

149
00:14:25,072 --> 00:14:27,157
I'm not new to this.

150
00:14:37,668 --> 00:14:39,753
You're just not good at reading people.

151
00:14:48,178 --> 00:14:50,014
Are you serious about this?

152
00:14:50,097 --> 00:14:51,640
No, that's not it.

153
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:53,767
Wait, that's wrong.

154
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:56,520
- Oh my God.
- Here.

155
00:14:57,563 --> 00:14:58,856
That's her.

156
00:15:14,788 --> 00:15:17,708
She is La Fornarina!

157
00:15:36,268 --> 00:15:38,395
But there's inconsistentency.

158
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:46,362
Why are you suddenly interested in Chiara?

159
00:16:04,588 --> 00:16:06,924
It felt like someone
was investigating her.

160
00:16:10,177 --> 00:16:11,679
A buddy.

161
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:34,868
But his tone

162
00:16:35,744 --> 00:16:37,246
wasn't admiration.

163
00:17:18,871 --> 00:17:20,039
We bring her in.

164
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:23,250
None, sir.

165
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:26,045
Tax-abiding, no criminal record,

166
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:28,630
not even a traffic violation.

167
00:17:37,848 --> 00:17:39,058
You know, I wouldn't be surprised

168
00:17:39,141 --> 00:17:40,934
if you and Bok
actually had something before.

169
00:17:41,727 --> 00:17:43,771
Because you think alike.

170
00:17:43,854 --> 00:17:47,441
You know, she was actually
the one who suggested before

171
00:17:47,524 --> 00:17:49,693
that we should kidnap Mikoy.

172
00:17:49,777 --> 00:17:51,028
Right, Bok?

173
00:17:51,111 --> 00:17:52,571
Shut up.

174
00:18:06,418 --> 00:18:07,795
How?

175
00:18:13,926 --> 00:18:15,552
What's your plan?

176
00:18:43,580 --> 00:18:46,041
- Good morning, ma'am.
- Hi, good morning.

177
00:18:57,177 --> 00:18:59,763
Sorry, I didn't see you.

178
00:19:23,078 --> 00:19:24,204
I won't allow it.

179
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:26,498
No, Alex, I won't agree
to that kind of set-up.

180
00:19:28,167 --> 00:19:29,877
It doesn't suit you.

181
00:19:29,960 --> 00:19:32,379
If you need a leading man
who has charisma,

182
00:19:32,462 --> 00:19:33,422
that's me.

183
00:19:33,505 --> 00:19:36,175
I'm way more handsome and more charming.

184
00:19:36,758 --> 00:19:38,177
Just being realistic.

185
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:41,138
Hey. This isn't a romcom, okay?

186
00:19:46,226 --> 00:19:48,061
Just surveillance for now.

187
00:20:05,245 --> 00:20:06,413
What's all this?

188
00:20:07,748 --> 00:20:09,958
It's like the floor is lava.

189
00:20:12,711 --> 00:20:16,965
Sorry, I didn't expect
to bring this much stuff.

190
00:20:17,049 --> 00:20:18,550
You didn't expect it?

191
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:20,093
Wow.

192
00:20:20,177 --> 00:20:21,595
It's a lot of stuff.

193
00:20:32,105 --> 00:20:33,815
So you actually know how to fold clothes?

194
00:20:34,942 --> 00:20:37,569
I'm the one who folds
and hangs Mom's laundry.

195
00:20:39,488 --> 00:20:41,406
Ah, lucky me indeed.

196
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:45,619
I even found a guy
who isn't afraid of house chores.

197
00:20:52,668 --> 00:20:53,877
Chiara, you know,

198
00:20:53,961 --> 00:20:55,379
we're like a married couple.

199
00:20:55,462 --> 00:20:56,964
You're moving too fast.

200
00:20:57,047 --> 00:20:57,965
How am I moving fast?

201
00:20:58,048 --> 00:21:00,300
You're the one who suddenly moved in.

202
00:21:03,303 --> 00:21:05,097
- Really?
- Don't you want me here anymore?

203
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:07,599
Hey, I never said that.

204
00:21:09,268 --> 00:21:11,311
Of course, I really want this.

205
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:28,996
I think you should get that now.

206
00:21:29,079 --> 00:21:29,913
Right now?

207
00:21:29,997 --> 00:21:30,831
Yes.

208
00:21:31,498 --> 00:21:32,958
Fine then.

209
00:22:38,065 --> 00:22:39,149
Chiara!

210
00:22:47,991 --> 00:22:49,201
Are you okay?

211
00:22:50,744 --> 00:22:51,745
Oh?

212
00:22:51,828 --> 00:22:53,080
I'm okay.

213
00:22:54,372 --> 00:22:55,957
Just hungry.

214
00:22:56,041 --> 00:22:56,958
Just hungry.

215
00:22:57,042 --> 00:22:58,210
Okay.

216
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:02,255
By the way, sweetheart,

217
00:23:03,465 --> 00:23:06,343
I really appreciate it, you know.

218
00:23:06,426 --> 00:23:08,303
You want me to rest,

219
00:23:08,386 --> 00:23:10,680
but I really don't think I can.

220
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:14,601
I'm just not used to doing nothing,

221
00:23:14,684 --> 00:23:17,437
and I also feel embarrassed
toward Papa Viktor.

222
00:23:17,521 --> 00:23:19,898
You know, I've already
missed so much at the office.

223
00:23:19,981 --> 00:23:24,236
They might think that I'm useless.

224
00:23:25,362 --> 00:23:27,280
So you want to work again?

225
00:23:30,242 --> 00:23:33,745
Just check in once in a while,
not full-time.

226
00:23:33,829 --> 00:23:36,915
You know, just dropping by
every now and then.

227
00:23:38,959 --> 00:23:39,835
Okay.

228
00:23:40,919 --> 00:23:41,837
Really?

229
00:23:44,548 --> 00:23:45,590
Okay.

230
00:23:47,968 --> 00:23:48,802
So, shall we?

231
00:23:48,885 --> 00:23:49,719
Let's eat.

232
00:23:57,769 --> 00:24:00,814
GLOBAL AGENCY FOR GOVERNMENT OPERATIONS

233
00:24:07,779 --> 00:24:09,364
I already scrubbed her profile.

234
00:24:09,447 --> 00:24:11,366
Carlota Regalo.

235
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:17,831
Clearly well-trained.

236
00:24:21,293 --> 00:24:22,711
She was never exposed.

237
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:26,381
There was also a hostage incident
in which she entered alone.

238
00:24:27,215 --> 00:24:30,343
She neutralized the two hostage takers

239
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:32,596
in close quarters.

240
00:24:35,307 --> 00:24:37,392
She got the hostages out…

241
00:24:38,768 --> 00:24:40,061
without firing a shot.

242
00:24:47,652 --> 00:24:48,945
Clean record.

243
00:24:56,912 --> 00:24:58,705
You won't notice her

244
00:24:58,788 --> 00:25:00,707
ulessshe wants to be noticed.

245
00:25:00,790 --> 00:25:02,667
She's like a chameleon.

246
00:25:04,044 --> 00:25:06,296
There were no red flags
during her service, either.

247
00:25:09,549 --> 00:25:11,259
Not even for being late.

248
00:25:14,512 --> 00:25:15,972
Surveillance first.

249
00:25:19,643 --> 00:25:20,602
Alex.

250
00:25:26,524 --> 00:25:28,026
It's uneven.

251
00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:31,321
Wow!

252
00:25:31,404 --> 00:25:33,198
I'm so lucky.

253
00:25:33,949 --> 00:25:34,908
Of course!

254
00:25:34,991 --> 00:25:37,869
I have a stylist and a personal chef too.

255
00:25:39,079 --> 00:25:41,790
Here. Don't buy food anymore.

256
00:25:41,873 --> 00:25:43,083
This tastes better.

257
00:25:45,835 --> 00:25:48,004
Oh, my! Sweetheart!

258
00:25:48,088 --> 00:25:50,882
You know, you're basically ready
to get married!

259
00:25:53,385 --> 00:25:55,512
All I'm missing is a groom.

260
00:25:57,347 --> 00:25:58,848
I see.

261
00:25:59,349 --> 00:26:00,600
So what am I?

262
00:26:00,684 --> 00:26:02,310
An intern or something?

263
00:26:07,482 --> 00:26:08,692
Wow, okay!

264
00:26:08,775 --> 00:26:11,486
You just moved in
and you already moved on?

265
00:26:11,569 --> 00:26:12,737
Like that?

266
00:26:12,821 --> 00:26:14,823
So, are you still hiring?

267
00:26:18,535 --> 00:26:20,662
Oh, I see.

268
00:26:20,745 --> 00:26:22,539
I'll pass. You're a red flag.

269
00:26:27,502 --> 00:26:28,837
Here.

270
00:26:32,132 --> 00:26:35,302
Oh, text me, okay, when you get there.

271
00:26:39,264 --> 00:26:40,598
I'll get going.

272
00:27:01,161 --> 00:27:02,245
Take care!

273
00:27:36,112 --> 00:27:37,655
<i>You were too late.</i>
<i>They already met someone.</i>

274
00:27:39,824 --> 00:27:41,451
<i>The one Viktor assigned to him.</i>

275
00:27:41,534 --> 00:27:45,497
<i>So you're telling me that Mikoy's</i>
<i>new assistant is an assassin?</i>

276
00:27:45,580 --> 00:27:46,748
<i>A killer?</i>

277
00:27:59,969 --> 00:28:02,514
<i>How did she know me?</i>
<i>How did she know my name?</i>

278
00:28:02,597 --> 00:28:04,099
Thank you so much!

279
00:28:04,182 --> 00:28:06,643
Of course! I'm so happy for you.

